âš™ï¸ Non-Static Field Initialization Order

When an object is created, Java initializes variables in this order:

1ï¸âƒ£ Default value â†’ All variables get default (like 0 or null).
2ï¸âƒ£ At declaration â†’ If initialized inline (int x = 100;).
3ï¸âƒ£ Non-static block â†’ If present, it updates the variable.
4ï¸âƒ£ Constructor â†’ Final custom initialization.
5ï¸âƒ£ Method body â†’ Only if you call it later (not during creation).

